 <H1>Representation of background knowledge</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Influences: A single factor that makes an outcome more likely:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>(easier 	(strong-actor)	(inflate balloon))
<LI>(easier	(more-elastic)	(inflate balloon))
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Inference Rules: How to recognize when factors are present
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>(act stretch)  	?	(more-elastic)
<LI>(old-actor) 	?	(strong-actor)
<LI>(age adult) 	?	(old-actor)
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Use of background knowledge
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Suggest hypotheses that are tested against further examples
<LI>Suggest revisions to inaccurate hypotheses 
<UL>
<LI>Multiple necessary causes
<LI>Multiple sufficient causes</UL></UL></UL></P>
